  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200\u00b0C (400\u00b0F). Toss chickpeas with olive oil, tandoori spice mix, smoked paprika, and chili powder. Spread on a baking sheet and roast for 20 minutes, stirring halfway, until golden and crisp.",
    "Remove chickpeas from oven and let cool to room temperature.",
    "Dice cucumber, thinly slice red onion, and slice green onions.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk chilled butter, lemon juice, and a pinch of salt and pepper until smooth.",
    "In a large bowl, combine roasted chickpeas, cucumber, onion, and green onion. Pour dressing over and toss gently.",
    "Add chopped cilantro and mix again.",
    "Transfer salad to the refrigerator and chill for at least 15 minutes before serving.",
    "Serve chilled, optionally garnishing with extra cilantro or a drizzle of olive oil."
  ],
